messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Um, yes, I need an ambulance.
What is the address of the emergency?
Um, I'm on Hardstone, in Rhode.
Okay, tell me what's happening there.
Um, my friend is passed out and he's not waking up at all.
How old is he?
He's 12.
What caused him to pass out?
I have no idea.
Is he breathing?
Um, he's coughing up orange stuff over and over and he won't wake up at all.
Did he take any medication?
No.
Okay. And you don't know what he was doing prior to this happening?
Hold on one second.
I have help on the way. Don't hang up, okay?
Alright.
Is he foaming at the mouth?
Yeah, he's foaming at the mouth.
Okay, is he breathing?
Yes.
What's he doing?
He's lying on his back, coughing really bad, so we put him on his side.
Did he take an overdose? Can you tell me what happened when you found him?
No, he wasn't on the floor. He was just sleeping. He was coughing really bad, so we went in there.
Was he sick before today?
No.
Okay. Well, we have help on the way. Don't give him anything to eat or drink; it might make him sick or cause problems for the doctor, okay?
That's the thing. He won't wake up.
But he is breathing, though?
Yeah.
How do you know he's breathing?
Because he's coughing, and you can see his chest moving.

Okay, I just want to make sure that he's breathing. If he's not breathing, then I need to stay on the phone with you. As long as he's breathing, we can wait for help to arrive. Is he still breathing now?
Yeah, he's breathing.
You can see his chest rising and falling normally, right?
Yes.
So you just heard him coughing, and then you went into the room and he was passed out?
Yeah.
They're on the way. I'm not stopping them from coming. Is there anything else that's happening right now?
I have to roll him over on his side. His mom can't do it.
Okay. Is his mom okay?
Yeah, she's fine.
Okay. Hold on one second. Don't hang up.
